RUNELF(1)

NAME
    runelf - run an ELF program and wait

SYNOPSIS
    runelf path [arg ...]

DESCRIPTION
    runelf is a shell built-in that executes an ext2 ELF program and waits for
    it to exit.

    The shell resolves command-style names in /bin, /usr/bin, and /usr/sbin.
    If path includes a slash, it is treated as a filesystem path. The .elf
    suffix may be omitted.

EXAMPLES
    runelf /usr/bin/hello.elf
    runelf hello

SEE ALSO
    runelf_nowait(1), runelf_bg(1), shell(1)
